Key Match Events: Shaheen Shah Afridi dismissed Andrew Balbirnie and Lorcan Tucker in the first over.
Pakistan finished the chase with seven balls to spare after a late partnership of 26 runs between Joshua Little and Benjamin White.
Babar Azam anchored Pakistan's innings with 32 not out.
Pre-Game Insights: Pakistan won the toss and chose to bowl.
Ireland had a poor start, losing their top order quickly.
The match was a dead rubber as both teams were already eliminated from Group A.
Post-Match Reflections: Babar Azam stated Pakistan 'have some good individuals but didn't play well as a team'.
Paul Stirling praised Ireland's fight but expressed confidence in the team's future.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was held at Lauderhill, a venue that had previously seen three washouts.
The win was Pakistan's second in the tournament but they finished third in Group A.
